  "markdown_content": "\n## Executive Summary\n\nUser requested testing of the Make connector and demonstration of its capabilities. Manus encountered OAuth authentication issues and provided guidance on proper setup requirements. The session revealed that Make connector requires pre-configured 'On demand' scenarios and proper authentication before use.\n\n\n## Context & Intent\n\nUser wanted to test and understand the Make connector's functionality and capabilities within the Manus system.\n\n\n## What Was Done\n\nAttempted to explore Make connector tools, diagnosed OAuth authentication failure, provided troubleshooting guidance and setup requirements.\n\n\n## Outputs Produced\n\n- [diagnostic] OAuth Error Analysis — Identified authentication issue with Make connector\n- [guidance] Setup Instructions — Step-by-step requirements for Make connector configuration\n\n## Key Decisions & Validations\n\n- Prioritized diagnostic approach over feature demonstration when authentication failed\n\n## Lessons Learned\n\nWorked well:\n\n- Clear error diagnosis\n- Proactive troubleshooting guidance\nFailed / suboptimal:\n\n- Make connector not properly authenticated\n- Unable to demonstrate actual capabilities\nDiscoveries:\n\n- Make connector requires 'On demand' scenarios\n- OAuth authentication is prerequisite for functionality\n\n## Challenges & Blockers\n\n- OAuth authentication not configured\n- No pre-existing Make scenarios set up\n\n## Open Questions\n\n- Does user have Make account properly connected?\n- Are there existing scenarios to test with?\n- Should we focus on setup guidance or wait for proper authentication?\n\n## Next Steps\n\n- User needs to configure Make account authentication\n- Create 'On demand' scenarios in Make platform\n- Retry connector testing after proper setup\n- Demonstrate actual capabilities once authenticated\n---\nUID: xXj0ErdOO86eqmPfAPMq3q | Model: claude-sonnet-4-20250514 | Cost: $0.0103\n"
